article.headline: Lady Monarchs down Georgia St. behind Canady's career-high 23
article.linkText: Canady's 23 carry Old Dominion past Georgia St.
article.story:
ATLANTA (AP) -- Jessica Canady scored a career-high 21 points to lead Old Dominion (No. 23 ESPN/USA Today, No. 19 AP) to a 79-59 win over Georgia State on Sunday in the Colonial Athletic Association opener for both teams.

ODU (10-3) improved to 16-1 in CAA openers.

Brittany Hollins led GSU (3-9) with a career-best 25 points. Shahida Williams added 12 points and eight rebounds for the Panthers.

The Lady Monarchs built a 35-24 halftime lead and broke the game open after Georgia State cut the deficit to 45-37 with 12:32 to play by going on a 12-2 run. Shay Rawls added 13 points and seven rebounds for Old Dominion.
